		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So why wasn't the epoxy blob technique the most commonly used by Nintendo ?</div>
<br />A few of the games that Nintendo wanted to replicate <em>really</em> cheap in <em>mass</em> quantities were glop-tops. Some of these were pack-in multicarts such as SMB1/Duck Hunt, SMB1/Duck Hunt/World Class Track Meet, Super Spike V'ball/World Cup.

		

